// Debian bookworm's packaged 50unattended-upgrades already ships an
// Origins-Pattern for the standard Debian-security origin — confirm that
// line is present after install (see SETUP.md verification step) rather
// than duplicating it here.
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot "false";

// Deliberately NOT adding Docker's own apt repo (download.docker.com,
// confirmed Origin: Docker) to the auto-patched origins. This repo already
// treats anything container-adjacent as deliberately manual/reviewed
// (pinned app image digests throughout) — Docker Engine is the substrate
// every app here runs on, so it gets the same manual-review treatment, not
// silent overnight auto-patching. OS-level security packages (kernel,
// openssh, glibc, etc.) still auto-patch via the origin above.
